==生平==
===球會===
;早年
Bolasie began his career with [[Rushden_&_Diamonds_F.C.|Rushden & Diamonds]] at the age of 16.<ref>[http://www.thisisplymouth.co.uk/argyle/Bolasie-completes-Argyle/article-225495-detail/article.html "Bolasie completes move to Argyle"] This is Plymouth, ''The Herald'', 17 July 2008; Retrieved 10 August 2010</ref> He spent four months as a member of their youth team and then had a spell with [[Hillingdon_Borough_F.C.|Hillingdon Borough]] before moving across Europe to play for [[Floriana_F.C.|Floriana]] in the [[Maltese_Premier_League|Maltese Premier League]].<ref>[http://www.thediamondsfc.com/page/ProfilesDetail/0,,10784~43988,00.html "Yannick Bolasie"] Rushden & Diamonds; Retrieved 10 August 2010 {{deadlink|date=April 2013}}</ref> He returned to England in 2008 after being offered a trial with [[Plymouth_Argyle_F.C.|Plymouth Argyle]], and impressed enough to be offered a two-year contract.<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/p/plymouth_argyle/7512355.stm "Teenager Bolasie opts for Argyle"] BBC Sport, 17 July 2008; Retrieved 10 August 2010</ref> He joined [[Dagenham_&_Redbridge_F.C.|Dagenham & Redbridge]] on trial, with a view to a loan move,<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/p/plymouth_argyle/7644168.stm "Bolasie back from Daggers trial"] BBC Sport, 30 September 2008; Retrieved 10 August 2010</ref> before returning to Rushden & Diamonds on loan near the end of the year.<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/r/rushden_and_diamonds/7742855.stm "Rushden sign Plymouth midfielder"] BBC Sport, 21 November 2008; Retrieved 10 August 2010</ref> He made his debut against [[Eastbourne_Borough_F.C.|Eastbourne Borough]] on 29 November,<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_conf/7727623.stm "Rushden 2–0 Eastbourne"] BBC Sport, 22 November 2008; Retrieved 10 August 2010</ref> and made seven appearances in the [[2008–09_Football_Conference|Conference]] before returning to Argyle in January 2009. Bolasie then joined [[Barnet_F.C.|Barnet]] on loan,<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/b/barnet/7845749.stm "Bolasie makes Barnet loan switch"] BBC Sport, 22 January 2009; Retrieved 10 August 2010</ref> making his [[Football_League|Football League]] debut against [[Accrington_Stanley_F.C.|Accrington Stanley]] on 24 January 2009.<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_div_3/7844305.stm "Accrington 1–1 Barnet"] BBC Sport, 23 January 2009; Retrieved 10 August 2010</ref> He scored his first goal two weeks later, opening the scoring in a 3–3 draw against [[Grimsby_Town_F.C.|Grimsby Town]].<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_div_3/7869550.stm "Barnet 3–3 Grimsby"] BBC Sport, 10 February 2009; Retrieved 10 August 2010</ref>

He returned to Argyle at the end of the [[2008–09_Football_League|2008–09 season]] having made 20 league appearances for Barnet, scoring three goals.<ref>[http://www.soccerbase.com/squad_season.sd?seasonid=138&teamid=344 "Barnet 2008/2009 player appearances"] Soccerbase; Retrieved 10 August 2010</ref> The club's manager, [[Ian_Hendon|Ian Hendon]], was keen to bring Bolasie back, but dismissed the chances of signing him permanently. "Yannick is still under contract at Plymouth, so it is likely that he will return there at the end of the season," he said.<ref>[http://www.skysports.com/story/0,19528,11705_5187907,00.html "Hendon keen to keep trio"] Sky Sports, 14 April 2009; Retrieved 10 August 2010</ref> He rejoined the Barnet squad in July 2009 ahead of the new season on a six month loan,<ref>[http://www.pafc.co.uk/page/NewsDetail/0,,10364~1719360,00.html "Benefit time"] Plymouth Argyle; Retrieved 10 August 2010 {{deadlink|date=April 2013}}</ref> and hoped it would act as a springboard to winning a place in the Argyle [[first_team|first team]].<ref>[http://www.skysports.com/story/0,19528,11688_5487285,00.html "Bolasie eyes Pilgrims future"] Sky Sports, 12 August 2009; Retrieved 10 August 2010</ref> He scored against Grimsby again in October 2009, capping a fine display with a fierce shot from 30 yards<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_div_3/8273393.stm "Barnet 3–0 Grimsby"] BBC Sport, 3 October 2009; Retrieved 10 August 2010</ref> Bolasie scored his second goal of the season three weeks later against [[Darlington_F.C.|Darlington]],<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_div_3/8306899.stm "Barnet 3–0 Darlington"] BBC Sport, 24 October 2009; Retrieved 10 August 2010</ref> as Hendon's side maintained a place in the top half of the [[2009–10_Football_League_Two|League Two]] table.<ref>[http://www.statto.com/football/teams/barnet/2009-2010 "2009–10 Barnet season"] Statto.com (Statto Organisation Limited) Retrieved 10 August 2010</ref>

;普利茅夫
Bolasie returned to Plymouth Argyle in January 2010,<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/b/barnet/8448445.stm "Bees Bolasie returns to Plymouth"] BBC Sport, 8 January 2010; Retrieved 10 August 2010</ref> having made a further 22 league appearances for Barnet, scoring twice.<ref>[http://www.soccerbase.com/teams/team.sd?team_id=344&teamTabs=stats "Barnet 2009/2010 player appearances"] Soccerbase; Retrieved 10 August 2010</ref> He was given a chance to impress by [[Paul_Mariner|Paul Mariner]], who had succeeded Sturrock a month earlier, and included him in the squad to take on [[Barnsley_F.C.|Barnsley]] on 13 February 2010.<ref>[http://www.thisiscornwall.co.uk/BENCH-DUTY-BOLASIE/story-11479994-detail/story.html#axzz2PDNjjqbs Bench duty for Bolasie] This is Cornwall (Local World), 16 February 2010</ref> He made his debut for the club in that game, coming off the substitute bench to provide the momentum to turn a one nil deficit into a 3–1 win for the visitors.<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_div_1/8508484.stm "Barnsley 1–3 Plymouth"] BBC Sport, 13 February 2010; Retrieved 13 February 2010</ref> He scored his first goal for the club two weeks later at [[Sheffield_United_F.C.|Sheffield United]].<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_div_1/8534714.stm "Sheff Utd 4–3 Plymouth"] BBC Sport, 27 February 2010; Retrieved 27 February 2010</ref> The pacy winger,<ref>[http://www.thisiscornwall.co.uk/Winger-Bolasie-Home-Park-hopes/story-11463509-detail/story.html#axzz2PDNjjqbs Winger Bolasie has Home Park hopes] This is Cornwall (Local World), 14 August 2009; Retrieved 1 April 2013</ref> ended the season with 16 [[2009–10_Football_League_Championship|Championship]] appearances to his name,<ref>[http://www.soccerbase.com/teams/team.sd?team_id=2036&teamTabs=stats "Plymouth 2009/2010 player appearances"] Soccerbase; Retrieved 10 August 2010</ref> but could not prevent the club from being relegated to [[Football_League_One|League One]]. Bolasie was offered a new contract by the club in April 2010,<ref>[http://www.skysports.com/story/0,19528,11095_6118172,00.html "Bolasie keen on new deal"] Sky Sports; 26 April 2010; Retrieved 10 August 2010</ref> and Bolasie signed it in July after the arrival of [[Peter_Reid|Peter Reid]] as the club's new manager.<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/p/plymouth_argyle/8777368.stm "Bolasie signs new deal at Argyle"] BBC Sport, 30 June 2010; Retrieved 10 August 2010</ref>

;布里斯托城
Bolasie was transferred to [[Bristol_City_F.C.|Bristol City]] on 6 June 2011 for an undisclosed fee and signed a two-year contract.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bristol City sign Plymouth Argyle's Yannick Bolasie|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/13595516.stm| publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=6 June 2011|date=6 June 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Bristol City manager Keith Millen delighted as Yannick Bolasie set to sign|url=http://www.thisisbristol.co.uk/Bristol-City-manager-Keith-Millen-delighted/story-12717390-detail/story.html|accessdate=6 June 2011|work= This is Bristol|publisher=Local World|date=6 June 2011}}</ref> He scored his first goal for the club in a 3–1 win against [[Coventry_City_F.C.|Coventry City]] on 9 April 2012.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bristol City 3–1 Coventry|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/17581337|work=BBC Sport|accessdate=22 April 2012|date=9 April 2012}}</ref> Prior to the match against Barnsley later that month, Bolasie was named Young Player of the Year by the Supporters Club and Trust after a fans vote.<ref>{{cite web|title=Jon Lands Top Fans' Award|url=http://www.bcfc.co.uk/page/NewsDetail/0,,10327~2743276,00.html|publisher=Bristol City F.C|accessdate=22 April 2012|date=21 April 2012}}</ref> He submitted a written transfer request in August 2012 because he wanted to move back to London.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bristol City's Yannick Bolasie submits transfer request|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/19312112|work=BBC Sport|publisher=BBC|accessdate=27 January 2013|date=19 August 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Yannick Bolasie asks to leave Bristol City as Crystal Palace wait to swoop|url=http://www.thisisbristol.co.uk/Yannick-Bolasie-asks-leave-Bristol-City-Crystal/story-16733203-detail/story.html|accessdate=27 January 2013|work=This is Bristol|publisher=Local World|date=19 August 2012}}</ref>

