In August 2012, Bolasie signed a three-year contract with [[Crystal_Palace_F.C.|Crystal Palace]] for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite web|title=Freedman Ties Up Bolasie Deal|url=http://www.cpfc.co.uk/news/article/moritz-joins-palace-332542.aspx|publisher=Crystal Palace F.C|accessdate=24 August 2012|date=24 August 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Crystal Palace sign Darcy Blake, Yannick Bolasie and Andre Mortiz|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/19360842|work=BBC Sport|publisher=BBC|accessdate=27 January 2013|date=24 August 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Crystal Palace sign Bristol City winger|url=http://www.ilfordrecorder.co.uk/sport/sport-football/crystal_palace_sign_bristol_city_winger_1_1494092|accessdate=27 January 2013|work=Ilford Recorder|publisher= Archant Community Media|date=24 August 2012}}</ref> He made his debut in a 2–1 defeat at [[Middlesbrough_F.C.|Middlesbrough]],<ref>{{cite news|last=Ritson|first=Mark|title=Darcy Blake, Yannick Bolasie and Andre Moritz impress Dougie Freedman|url=http://www.thisiscroydontoday.co.uk/Darcy-Blake-Yannick-Bolasie-Andre-Moritz-impress/story-16771217-detail/story.html|accessdate=27 January 2013|work=This is Croydon Today|publisher=Local World|date=27 August 2012}}</ref> and scored his first goal for Palace in a 5–0 win against [[Ipswich_Town_F.C.|Ipswich Town]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Ashton|first=Tim|title=Holloway enthused by "absolutely fantastic" five-star Palace |url=http://www.croydonguardian.co.uk/sport/eagleeye/10030958.Eagles_top_the_Championship__and_Holloway_could_not_be_happier/ |publisher=Newsquest |accessdate=27 January 2013|work=Croydon Guardian|date=7 November 2012}}</ref>

